Folwarki  is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Cieszanów, within Lubaczów County, Subcarpathian Voivodeship, in south-eastern Poland. It lies approximately  south-west of Cieszanów,  north of Lubaczów, and  east of the regional capital Rzeszów.
